Summary
Funnel analysis identified a major drop-off at the top of the funnel, with only ~23% of users viewing products after landing. Device-level analysis showed consistent performance across platforms, ruling out UX issues as the primary driver. Further segmentation by traffic source revealed that direct and internal traffic convert significantly better (~42–53%) compared to Google and other channels (~39–41%), indicating that the main issue lies in low-intent traffic acquisition rather than product or checkout experience.

Recommendation 1 — Fix traffic quality:
refine ad targeting
align landing pages with intent
reduce low-quality acquisition sources

Recommendation 2 — Improve top-of-funnel engagement:
better homepage UX
clearer product discovery
stronger value proposition

Recommendation 3 — Leverage high-intent users:
retarget direct users
email campaigns
remarketing
